WEBVTT

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:51.300
The star fell, Bull.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:54.040
That is no ordinary star.

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:56.270
That is the tear of a warrior.

00:01:56.310 --> 00:01:58.540
What is a warrior?

00:01:58.580 --> 00:02:02.310
One who has finished his battle
somewhere on this planet…

00:02:04.150 --> 00:02:10.180
A pitiful soul that could not
believe in the Great Spirit…

00:02:42.790 --> 00:02:46.320
The report from Callisto went
directly to Sir Vicious.

00:02:46.830 --> 00:02:48.820
He is requesting a deal for Red-Eye.

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:52.560
30,000 Woolongs per gram.
A total of 7500 grams.

00:02:53.440 --> 00:02:56.670
Why did he specify you as the dealer?

00:02:56.710 --> 00:03:01.270
He is a Titan veteran.
We were in the same unit.

00:03:01.310 --> 00:03:04.110
Why does he rely on you now?

00:03:04.150 --> 00:03:06.940
Callisto is undergoing
a depression right now.

00:03:06.980 --> 00:03:09.320
If he can’t see the future,
he is sure to worry.

00:03:09.650 --> 00:03:13.250
All the more reason to keep
our hands out of that moon.

00:03:13.290 --> 00:03:16.820
Vicious, are you not
the one that is worrying?

00:03:17.290 --> 00:03:21.700
You have no permission to
make your own decisions.

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:27.000
Regardless of who it is, those who go
against the Van’s will are punished.

00:03:27.940 --> 00:03:30.630
You believe that I would
betray my own mentor?

00:03:30.670 --> 00:03:33.270
Mao’s case was merely bad luck.

00:03:35.540 --> 00:03:39.110
Lin… You shall go with Vicious.

00:03:39.650 --> 00:03:40.480
Yes.

00:03:40.520 --> 00:03:41.570
Wang Long!

00:03:41.620 --> 00:03:44.420
Callisto is a frigid planet.

00:03:44.450 --> 00:03:48.150
Take plenty of winter clothes.

00:03:48.190 --> 00:03:51.490
To me, no cold climate is
worth taking precautions for.

00:03:51.530 --> 00:03:55.690
It is true that the planet
is warmer than your heart.

00:03:56.100 --> 00:03:58.970
Your heart is colder
than a snake’s skin.

00:04:06.240 --> 00:04:07.800
Vicious.

00:04:10.510 --> 00:04:13.450
A snake cannot eat a dragon.

00:04:24.760 --> 00:04:27.130
I will be fine by myself.

00:04:27.160 --> 00:04:28.600
I’ll go with you.

00:04:28.630 --> 00:04:29.860
Remember this.

00:04:29.900 --> 00:04:34.200
If you want to survive,
you must betray me at times.

00:04:34.270 --> 00:04:35.760
No, never.

00:04:35.810 --> 00:04:38.210
That would go against the Van’s will.

00:04:38.240 --> 00:04:40.730
Such old-fashioned thinking
makes me nauseous.

00:04:41.080 --> 00:04:42.980
Those damn corpses!

00:04:43.010 --> 00:04:46.910
I will protect you,
for the honor of the Red Dragon.

00:04:47.120 --> 00:04:48.410
Honor, huh?

00:04:48.450 --> 00:04:52.220
Then, it’s up to me
to slaughter them all!

00:05:03.380 --> 00:05:07.890
JUPITER JAZZ (Part I)

00:05:11.790 --> 00:05:14.090
It’s hot…

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:21.630
Where are the others?

00:05:23.200 --> 00:05:26.170
What a depressing bunch…

00:05:33.010 --> 00:05:34.880
What’s with this humidity?

00:05:35.410 --> 00:05:37.880
It’s so muggy that I can’t sleep!

00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:41.220
Oh, it’s just a breakdown.

00:05:42.820 --> 00:05:45.310
It’d be hard for me to do
if I saw your faces…

00:05:45.390 --> 00:05:49.920
…so I’m leaving without seeing you one
last time. Please don’t look for me.

00:05:49.960 --> 00:05:51.430
That wench…

00:05:52.130 --> 00:05:55.330
She sucked out all the
antifreeze from the radiator.

00:05:55.400 --> 00:05:56.800
It’ll be out for at least half a day.

00:05:56.870 --> 00:06:00.030
Even if she didn’t pull this stunt
we wouldn’t look for her. Right?

00:06:00.640 --> 00:06:02.110
She emptied out the safe as well.

00:06:07.150 --> 00:06:11.640
7, 8, 9… hello!

00:06:11.720 --> 00:06:14.020
Are you really looking for Faye?

00:06:14.050 --> 00:06:17.820
1, 0, 1, 1, goodbye!

00:06:17.860 --> 00:06:19.290
Are you just wasting time?

00:06:19.360 --> 00:06:21.260
Is there anything else to do right now?

00:06:21.260 --> 00:06:23.060
—Ooh! Boom!
—You found her?!

00:06:23.830 --> 00:06:26.130
I wonder who this is…

00:06:26.130 --> 00:06:29.070
Lesse… code name…

00:06:29.100 --> 00:06:30.530
Julia!

00:06:33.270 --> 00:06:34.830
Where is that coming from?!

00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:36.170
Lesse…

00:06:36.240 --> 00:06:37.710
Pretty close…

00:06:37.740 --> 00:06:40.270
Looks like Blue Crow on Callisto…

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:41.570
Where’s it going to?

00:06:43.020 --> 00:06:44.780
It got disconnected…

00:06:46.290 --> 00:06:46.720
Hey!

00:06:46.750 --> 00:06:48.220
But…

00:06:48.250 --> 00:06:50.450
Actually, there are no
girls in Blue Crow.

00:06:50.490 --> 00:06:52.290
Honestly…

00:06:52.290 --> 00:06:53.760
Hey, Spike…

00:06:53.790 --> 00:06:56.260
Is that it?

00:07:07.670 --> 00:07:08.440
Hey!

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:09.740
Hey, wait, Spike!

00:07:10.480 --> 00:07:14.000
That’s a common woman’s name!

00:07:14.080 --> 00:07:15.570
What about Faye?

00:07:15.610 --> 00:07:16.950
Leave her.

00:07:16.980 --> 00:07:18.680
This is a lawless area.

00:07:18.720 --> 00:07:21.480
A woman surely can’t survive
wandering about all alone!

00:07:21.520 --> 00:07:22.710
Feeling sympathetic?

00:07:22.790 --> 00:07:26.380
Plenty of sympathy…
for the money she ran away with!

00:07:28.230 --> 00:07:29.560
Spike!

00:07:33.830 --> 00:07:34.800
I’m gonna go look.

00:07:34.800 --> 00:07:35.990
What?

00:07:36.500 --> 00:07:38.800
I’m gonna look for my woman.

00:07:38.840 --> 00:07:41.710
You can look for that other woman.

00:07:41.740 --> 00:07:45.200
You’re gonna have nothing
to do with this?

00:07:46.350 --> 00:07:49.970
That’s right. We only go so far.

00:07:51.150 --> 00:07:53.310
Even if you come back, there
won’t be a place for you here.

00:07:54.550 --> 00:07:55.520
Can’t do anything about it.

00:07:56.890 --> 00:08:00.720
I’m sure you’re not as lonely now
that you have more strange roommates.

00:08:00.760 --> 00:08:02.190
Me?

00:08:02.230 --> 00:08:04.360
You stayed here just for that reason?

00:08:04.400 --> 00:08:05.990
You’re being stupid!

00:08:06.470 --> 00:08:09.090
It’s been three years
since I teamed up with you.

00:08:09.130 --> 00:08:13.000
But I never knew you
looked at me that way!

00:08:13.040 --> 00:08:17.370
I was under the impression
that you were the lonely one!

00:08:17.410 --> 00:08:19.240
Well we got rid of
that misunderstanding.

00:08:19.280 --> 00:08:22.440
Good riddance!!
Now we’ll have more money for food!

00:08:24.380 --> 00:08:26.850
I never did understand you,
even to the very end!

00:08:27.420 --> 00:08:29.940
I don’t understand, either.

00:08:30.290 --> 00:08:32.520
So long!

00:09:53.940 --> 00:09:55.800
I don’t know any woman.

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:57.740
Like I would know!

00:09:57.780 --> 00:09:58.940
Not even a rumor?

00:09:58.980 --> 00:10:01.450
I have no luck with ’em!

00:10:01.480 --> 00:10:05.080
I’d rather be with an armadillo!

00:10:05.120 --> 00:10:07.240
Have you heard of the name Julia?

00:10:07.290 --> 00:10:09.350
You shoulda said so earlier!

00:10:09.390 --> 00:10:12.590
There’s one in front of
Tony’s place every night!

00:10:17.700 --> 00:10:20.530
Excuse me! I’m not Julia.

00:10:20.570 --> 00:10:23.230
Ju-li-us! I’m Julius!

00:10:24.070 --> 00:10:25.230
Oh, I see…

00:10:25.800 --> 00:10:27.670
Hey, you’re my type.

00:10:27.710 --> 00:10:29.400
Wanna hang out with me tonight?

00:10:29.440 --> 00:10:31.430
I’m sorry, I already have plans.

00:10:31.810 --> 00:10:35.440
Oh, yeah. Gren might know something…

00:10:35.480 --> 00:10:38.350
I’ve seen him with a woman before.

00:10:38.380 --> 00:10:39.510
Gren?

00:10:39.550 --> 00:10:40.680
It’s cold.

00:10:40.720 --> 00:10:42.380
Looks like this is it for tonight.

00:10:42.420 --> 00:10:43.720
Oh, a customer?

00:10:43.760 --> 00:10:46.820
Not even. Can’t you tell he’s straight?

00:10:46.860 --> 00:10:48.690
Come on, let’s switch locations.

00:10:48.730 --> 00:10:50.750
Hey, who and where is Gren?

00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:53.200
So you wanna hang out with me tonight?

00:10:56.300 --> 00:11:00.170
He’s a sax player in Blue Crow.

00:11:12.790 --> 00:11:14.450
Take care.

00:11:18.090 --> 00:11:19.520
That was close.

00:11:21.030 --> 00:11:23.430
When someone sneezes
and doesn’t get told…

00:11:23.460 --> 00:11:25.990
…to take care, that
person becomes a fairy…

00:11:26.030 --> 00:11:28.690
That’s what they say around here.

00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:30.360
Then it’s okay.

00:11:30.400 --> 00:11:32.560
I’m already a fairy.

00:11:40.250 --> 00:11:42.870
I’m not as easy as I appear to be.

00:11:43.250 --> 00:11:45.720
Unfortunately, I am not
interested in women…

00:11:45.750 --> 00:11:47.380
Oh, that’s a shame…

00:11:47.420 --> 00:11:51.480
But the others seem to
be highly interested.

00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:55.420
You didn’t know that there
were no women in this town?

00:11:58.260 --> 00:11:59.890
So I’ll be very popular…

00:12:00.300 --> 00:12:03.270
You should watch out…

00:12:05.200 --> 00:12:08.110
Thanks for the warning.

00:12:22.350 --> 00:12:25.020
I’m searching for something…

00:12:29.760 --> 00:12:31.750
There’s nothing here.

00:12:31.800 --> 00:12:35.730
The only things are stale bread,
a broken-down car, and rancid booze.

00:12:36.170 --> 00:12:37.760
I’m looking for a guy named Gren.

00:12:37.800 --> 00:12:39.600
No idea.

00:12:39.640 --> 00:12:41.330
I see.

00:13:09.430 --> 00:13:11.990
Hey, you need something?

00:13:13.140 --> 00:13:14.630
You’re Vicious, right?

00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:15.500
Me?!

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:16.930
Where’s the money?

00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:19.740
If ya don’t put out,
it won’t do ya any good!

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:24.350
This is annoying…

00:13:24.380 --> 00:13:26.350
So annoying it’s repulsive!

00:13:54.880 --> 00:13:56.310
What the hell do you mean?!

00:13:58.120 --> 00:14:00.050
Why the hell am I Vicious?

00:14:00.850 --> 00:14:05.290
There was info that there was
gonna be some deal for Red-Eye.

00:14:05.360 --> 00:14:07.480
From Gren to Vicious.

00:14:07.530 --> 00:14:10.220
I thought of taking that cash…

00:14:11.430 --> 00:14:14.300
You think I look like I got money?

00:14:14.300 --> 00:14:16.270
Foreigners are all rich.

00:14:17.700 --> 00:14:18.970
And the code name was Julia?

00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:23.340
Heh… Sure sounds like
some easy wench’s name!

00:14:23.380 --> 00:14:24.710
Yeah… really.

00:14:32.720 --> 00:14:34.320
Gimme a Cowboy.

00:14:34.320 --> 00:14:36.910
There are no bounties around here.

00:14:36.990 --> 00:14:39.460
Bourbon with milk.

00:14:39.490 --> 00:14:44.260
Oh, That Cowboy. I knew that.
You can’t possibly be a bounty-hunter.

00:14:47.030 --> 00:14:49.000
<i>So, who’s our customer today?</i>

00:14:49.030 --> 00:14:52.370
<i>Grencia Mars Elijah Guo Eckener.</i>

00:14:52.400 --> 00:14:53.670
<i>That’s a long name!</i>

00:14:53.710 --> 00:14:55.760
<i>Yeah. He escaped from military,</i>
<i>prison three years ago…</i>

00:14:55.810 --> 00:14:57.870
<i>…and the statute of limitations</i>
<i>is about to expire.</i>

00:14:57.910 --> 00:14:58.770
<i>…and that means?</i>

00:14:58.810 --> 00:15:01.940
<i>The bounty is double!</i>

00:15:03.120 --> 00:15:05.050
<i>This is a chance you can’t miss!</i>

00:15:05.080 --> 00:15:08.710
<i>But I kinda feel like</i>
<i>we can let him go…</i>

00:15:08.750 --> 00:15:10.950
<i>Judy, what are you saying?</i>

00:15:10.990 --> 00:15:12.980
<i>He’s an escaped convict!</i>

00:15:13.030 --> 00:15:14.560
<i>But Punch…</i>

00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:17.360
<i>He’s very handsome!</i>

00:15:17.600 --> 00:15:19.430
<i>Just look at his picture!</i>

00:15:19.460 --> 00:15:21.360
<i>Lesse… Oh, come on…</i>

00:15:21.400 --> 00:15:23.330
<i>I’m much more handsome than he is…</i>

00:15:23.370 --> 00:15:25.860
<i>Punch, I just can’t</i>
<i>laugh at that joke…</i>

00:15:26.410 --> 00:15:28.430
Hey, can you turn that thing off?!

00:15:28.470 --> 00:15:30.530
Well, calm down.

00:15:30.580 --> 00:15:32.200
I’m sorry, man.

00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:36.940
Don’t worry. That guy passed
out over there is a cop.

00:15:36.980 --> 00:15:38.570
What do ya wanna say?

00:15:38.620 --> 00:15:41.420
Actually, there’s a
bounty on my head, too.

00:15:41.450 --> 00:15:43.790
This place is a hideout
for people like that.

00:15:43.820 --> 00:15:44.750
I see…

00:15:44.790 --> 00:15:48.090
So you can rest assured.

00:15:48.690 --> 00:15:49.320
Me?

00:15:59.300 --> 00:16:00.430
What’s with this?

00:16:00.470 --> 00:16:05.100
I wanted to get rid of all this
frustration, and nobody’s coming?

00:16:05.140 --> 00:16:07.740
Oh… you’re all here.

00:16:08.550 --> 00:16:11.950
Miss, your appearance is
rather harmful to the eyes.

00:16:11.980 --> 00:16:14.040
Or are you enticing us?

00:16:14.090 --> 00:16:15.520
Yeah, I am…

00:16:15.890 --> 00:16:17.510
Hold on a minute.

00:16:17.960 --> 00:16:21.450
If I don’t do this, I’ll chip a nail…

00:16:21.930 --> 00:16:23.930
Okay, any time now!

00:16:23.930 --> 00:16:25.690
You wench!

00:16:31.640 --> 00:16:32.900
Hurry!

00:17:05.270 --> 00:17:07.430
Why did you bring me here?

00:17:07.470 --> 00:17:10.530
Because you said you’re a fairy.

00:17:10.580 --> 00:17:12.130
Why did you come with me?

00:17:12.180 --> 00:17:14.540
’Cuz I got no place to stay.

00:17:14.580 --> 00:17:16.510
You can trust me that easily?

00:17:16.550 --> 00:17:19.070
You said you weren’t
interested in women.

00:17:19.120 --> 00:17:21.640
I might take your money and kill you…

00:17:22.090 --> 00:17:23.490
That’s fine.

00:17:23.520 --> 00:17:25.990
I’ve lived longer than I seem.

00:17:36.370 --> 00:17:38.460
It’s broken.

00:17:40.840 --> 00:17:43.910
You came to such a slummy
neighborhood all by yourself?

00:17:43.910 --> 00:17:45.210
I’m alone.

00:17:45.210 --> 00:17:47.180
I don’t want comrades…

00:17:47.210 --> 00:17:49.510
…and it’s not worth having any…

00:17:50.180 --> 00:17:54.140
I end up worrying about
things I don’t have to…

00:17:54.190 --> 00:17:57.450
You know, ’cuz I’m
such a good woman…

00:17:58.860 --> 00:18:01.790
All the guys end up fighting for me.

00:18:04.800 --> 00:18:09.320
They often say that humans
can’t live alone…

00:18:09.370 --> 00:18:12.630
But you can live pretty
long by yourself.

00:18:15.570 --> 00:18:18.840
Instead of feeling alone in a group…

00:18:18.880 --> 00:18:22.310
…it’s better to be alone
in your solitude.

00:18:23.050 --> 00:18:27.950
When I’m dealing with them,
it’s nothing but trouble…

00:18:29.090 --> 00:18:32.180
And I don’t get squat out of it…

00:18:32.220 --> 00:18:35.090
So it doesn’t matter if
I’m there or not…

00:18:35.590 --> 00:18:40.050
You just got scared of losing them.

00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:46.030
So you distanced yourself from them.

00:18:47.770 --> 00:18:49.430
You’re weird.

00:18:49.470 --> 00:18:50.840
Think so?

00:18:50.880 --> 00:18:53.870
I don’t know why I’m
talking to you about this…

00:18:56.380 --> 00:18:59.110
I feel like I’m in a confessional…

00:18:59.150 --> 00:19:01.350
Have you ever had
experience as a minister?

00:19:01.820 --> 00:19:03.340
No…

00:19:17.540 --> 00:19:18.590
Take care.

00:19:19.940 --> 00:19:21.270
You want to take a shower?

00:19:21.310 --> 00:19:22.570
No thanks.

00:19:22.610 --> 00:19:26.300
I don’t know where
peeping toms might be…

00:19:27.580 --> 00:19:29.010
You shouldn’t peek, either.

00:19:29.680 --> 00:19:31.340
Hm, I can’t guarantee that.

00:20:21.300 --> 00:20:23.030
<i>Gren… You’re not there?</i>

00:20:24.070 --> 00:20:25.760
Vicious?!

00:20:26.070 --> 00:20:27.770
<i>I’m out with “honroutou”.</i>

00:20:27.810 --> 00:20:33.400
<i>Along with the “mangan” and the</i>
<i>“ura-dora”, it’s 32000. I’ll be waiting.</i>

00:20:39.420 --> 00:20:41.650
Are you dating Julia behind my back?

00:20:43.660 --> 00:20:44.620
Sir Spike!

00:20:45.190 --> 00:20:48.320
Hey, Lin. You’ve gotten pretty big.

00:20:48.360 --> 00:20:51.820
He used to work under you,
but things are different now.

00:20:52.230 --> 00:20:56.390
I feel sorry for her. Having her name
used for some crooked deal like this.

00:20:56.840 --> 00:20:59.630
You were always the one
leaving others out of the loop.

00:21:02.710 --> 00:21:05.010
We still haven’t settled
the score from earlier.

00:21:06.850 --> 00:21:08.340
Any time.

00:21:08.950 --> 00:21:09.810
Lin!

00:21:23.190 --> 00:21:24.590
Get out of the way, Lin!

00:21:26.060 --> 00:21:28.330
Julia was here, in this town.

00:21:29.930 --> 00:21:31.660
Hey, out of the way, Lin!

00:21:34.670 --> 00:21:35.730
Lin…

00:21:44.350 --> 00:21:46.650
A woman?

00:21:46.650 --> 00:21:48.020
W-Which are you?

00:21:54.360 --> 00:21:57.330
I am both, but I am neither.

00:22:41.860 --> 00:22:47.290
Aishiteta to nageku niwa…
Too much time has passed by…

00:22:47.330 --> 00:22:53.630
…amarinimo toki wa sugite shimatta
…to lament that we were deeply in love.

00:22:53.670 --> 00:22:59.330
Mada kokoro no hokorobi wo…
The wind keeps blowing, while my heart…

00:22:59.370 --> 00:23:06.070
…iyasenu mama kaze ga fuiteru
…cannot heal all the tears in it.

00:23:06.110 --> 00:23:15.320
Kawaita hitomi de dareka naite kure
Someone, cry for me with parched eyes.

00:23:16.920 --> 00:23:20.330
The real folk blues.

00:23:20.330 --> 00:23:28.740
Honto no kanashimi ga shiritai dake
I only want to know what true sadness is.

00:23:28.770 --> 00:23:36.370
Doro no kawa ni tsukatta…
Sitting in muddy water…

00:23:36.410 --> 00:23:40.870
…jinsei mo waruku wa nai…
…isn’t such a bad life…

00:23:40.910 --> 00:23:49.790
…ichido kiri de owaru nara…
…if it ends after the first time…

00:24:05.730 --> 00:24:06.290
COMING EPISODE

00:24:06.290 --> 00:24:06.690
Hey… How are men and women different?
COMING EPISODE

00:24:06.690 --> 00:24:09.320
Hey… How are men and women different?

00:24:09.460 --> 00:24:13.900
Hmm… I think women are hiding
more vital things than men are.

00:24:13.930 --> 00:24:17.270
Yeah… but there are women
that aren’t feminine.

00:24:17.300 --> 00:24:18.930
And there are men
that aren’t masculine.

00:24:18.970 --> 00:24:21.400
What about those that
aren’t normally feminine…

00:24:21.440 --> 00:24:23.870
…but show that side on
some chance circumstance?

00:24:23.910 --> 00:24:24.930
I like that.

00:24:24.980 --> 00:24:25.600
Oh?

00:24:25.640 --> 00:24:26.940
I’m not talking about you.

00:24:26.980 --> 00:24:28.040
Then who?

00:24:28.080 --> 00:24:29.940
Maybe it’s Ed!

00:24:29.980 --> 00:24:31.720
Next episode: “Jupiter Jazz, part 2.”

00:24:31.720 --> 00:24:33.010
JUPITER JAZZ (Part II)
Next episode: “Jupiter Jazz, part 2.”

00:24:33.010 --> 00:24:33.050
JUPITER JAZZ (Part II)

00:24:33.050 --> 00:24:34.760
Maybe it’s me.
